The Israeli authorities argue that in that small town in the south of the enclave, on the border with Egypt and where 1,4 million inhabitants of Gaza were refugees, there are still four battalions of Hamas. Netanyahu has reiterated since the beginning of the devastating war that the invasion of Rafah is necessary not only to eliminate Hamas, but to ensure that Gaza ceases to constitute a "threat" for Israel.
